  <summary>11/17/2004--Introduced.
United Nations Accountability Act of 2004 - States that Congress urges the President to instruct the Permanent Mission of the United States to the United Nations (UN) to seek to ensure that all UN Office of Internal Oversight Services are made available to member nations. Directs the Secretary of State to report on UN officials' financial disclosure requirements.</summary>
